## Overview

This system captures **client-side UI errors** in React applications and forwards them to a backend logging API (e.g., Splunk forwarder or a DB logging service). The backend is out of scope for this document.

**What gets captured:**

- React component render errors (via ErrorBoundary)
- Unhandled Promise rejections
- Global JavaScript runtime errors
- Optional: manual logError() calls from anywhere in the app

**What does NOT get captured here:**

- Network/API errors (handle those in your API layer)
- Backend server errors
- Build-time errors

---

## How It Works

React Component Tree
        |
        | (throws during render / lifecycle)
        v
  ErrorBoundary (wraps App or sections)
        |
        v
  errorLoggerService.send(payload)
        |
        v
  POST /api/log/ui-error   <- Backend handles Splunk/DB persistence

Additionally, window.onerror and window.onunhandledrejection catch errors outside the React tree (e.g., async callbacks, setTimeout, third-party scripts).

