## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

- throw inside componentDidCatch -> never throw in the catch handler (infinite loop)
- console.error as the only logging -> always send to backend in production
- Showing stack traces to end users -> show only errorId to user
- Blocking render while logging -> use fire-and-forget async with silent catch
- Single boundary at root only -> use granular boundaries for isolated fallbacks
- Logging PII in error messages -> sanitize before sending
- Hard-coding the log URL -> always use environment variables

